## Step 7 — Asset Resolution

HTML files reference assets via local paths that won't resolve in Remotion.

| Asset type | Resolution |
|-----------|------------|
| Logo SVG | Use `<PilocLogo />` from `./Icons` — never `<img>` or `staticFile()` |
| Icon SVGs | Extract `<path d="...">` from HTML `<symbol>` tags into `Icons.tsx` |
| Product screenshots | Not needed — you're rebuilding as TSX |
| Avatar photos | Replace with colored circle + initials |
| Background images | Not needed — background is flat `T.navy` |
| Fonts | Always Inter via `waitForInter()` — never a local font file |

---

## Checklist before writing any TSX

- [ ] State machine map written (states, order, trigger events)
- [ ] Story Map written (protagonist, flow, value moment, essential components)
- [ ] Real data extracted verbatim (KPI values, row data, amounts, names, dates)
- [ ] Brand tokens mapped to `const T`
- [ ] Interaction map written (cursor waypoints, click targets, frame estimates)
- [ ] Component list finalized (3–5 items, chrome excluded)
- [ ] Card widths decided per scene
- [ ] `references/patterns` read — all animation patterns ready to use
